HEADWORD: Soursop
<hw>Sour"sop`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The large succulent and slightly acid fruit of a small tree
(<spn>Anona muricata</spn>) of the West Indies; also, the tree itself.
It is closely allied to the custard apple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sourwood</ent>⟦br⟧
